The transaction has received approval from the National Agency for Mineral Resources (NAMR) of Romania. The deal comes immediately after earlier in June 2015, Canadian oil and gas company Sterling Resources has sold its 40% interest in Block 27 Muridava to Petroceltic Romania B.V. for a non-material consideration. In the same time, Australian oil and gas company Beach Energy has also transferred its 30% interest in Block 28 Est Cobalcescu to Petroceltic Romania BV. Romania's NAMR approved both transfers. In a separate deal, in March 2015, Sterling Resources announced the sale of its entire Romanian business to U.S. alternative asset manager The Carlyle Group for a total cash consideration of USD 42.5mn (EUR 38.8mn). The transfer of the oil concession license in Block 27 Muridava to Petroceltic Romania BV was contemplated by the recently announced agreement with Carlyle and has no impact on the sale to Carlyle. Following the transaction, Petroceltic International will exit the Romanian market. The transaction is in line with Petroceltic International's strategy to exit from high risk exploration ventures and to focus its production and exploration efforts on Egypt and Italy. Petroceltic International is an upstream oil and gas exploration and production company, focused on the Middle East, North Africa and the Mediterranean Basin. ORIGINAL: Russian financial and industrial holding company BIN Group has agreed to acquire 100% in non-state pension fund Raiffeisen (NPF Raiffeisen) from Austrian Raiffeisen Bank International (RBI), the latter announced. The transaction value was not specified. The deal is pending regulatory approvals from the Federal Antimonopoly Service and the Central Bank. Raiffeisen Bank motivates the sale with its desire to focus on its core banking business, bearing in mind the current consolidation trend of players on the pension market. The shareholder change will not affect the obligations of the fund to clients and will not lead to a procedure for renewal of customer contracts. Also, Raiffeisen Bank will continue to service the fund's customers through its offices, and will also act as an agent for the sale of contracts of compulsory pension insurance in the future. In Q1 2015, NPF Raiffeisen entered the TOP 20 list of pension funds in terms of savings and reserves, according to statistics published by Russia's Central Bank. As of 31 May 2015, NPF Raiffeisen reported total assets under management of RUB 33.6bn (USD 640.6mn). The fund implements non-state pension projects for individuals and legal entities. It also participates in the mandatory pension insurance, including the government programme of co-financing of pension savings. BIN Group, controlled by the Gutseriev family, unites assets in the sectors of banking, oil production and processing, real estate development and retail trade. BIN Group controls several pension funds: NPF European Pension Fund, NPF Doverie, NPF Education and Science, as well as NPF Regionfund. The total volume of the group's pension savings exceeds RUB 100bn (USD 1.82bn). ORIGINAL: Hungarian state-owned gas distributor Fogaz announced it will take over the local regulated natural gas retail business units of Germany's E.ON (E.ON Energiaszolgáltató Kft.) and of France's GDF Suez (GDF SUEZ Energia Magyarország Zrt.). Financial details were not disclosed. The deal has been approved by the Hungarian Energy and Utilities Regulatory Office (MEKH). Fogaz submitted the only offer for E.ON and GDF Suez retail gas customers, after both companies requested the withdrawal of their universal service provider licenses to supply gas to households. Universal service providers supply gas using a price structure and level controlled by the state. The deal is in line with Fogaz's strategy to become the sole gas services supplier on the regulated market in the country. Through the deal, Fogaz will expand its services in 12 additional counties and will add around 1.3 million customers to its portfolio. E.ON Energiaszolgáltató Kft. has spun-off in January 2014 from E.ON Hungária Zrt. to operate in Hungary the universal electricity and gas trading activities within the E.ON Group. Its gas distribution network covers an area of 26,145 km2, serving more than 600,000 customers. E.ON Energiakereskedelmi Kft. took the competitive market for electricity and gas trading activities in the country. GDF SUEZ Energia Magyarország Zrt., formerly known as Égáz-Dégáz Zrt., engages in the distribution of natural gas, for consumers entitled for universal service. It operates in the north-west and the south-east region of Hungary, serving more than 750,000 customers. Fogaz provides natural gas trade on both the regulated retail market (to consumers entitled for universal service) as well as on the free market in Hungary. The company is also involved in developing modern heating systems, preserving cultural values and boosting cultural activities. Its shareholders include Hungarian state-owned energy company MVM (Magyar Villamos Muvek) with 49.83% stake and the Municipality of Budapest with 50% stake. Fogaz reported consolidated revenues of HUF 218.8bn (USD 781.6mn) in 2013. GDF Suez is engaged in the electricity generation and distribution, natural gas and renewable energy. It operates in 70 countries and has over 140,000 employees worldwide. In 2014, it reported revenues of EUR 74.7bn. E.ON SE is a global energy holding, active in power generation, oil and gas exploration and production, gas storage and transport, sale and distribution of energy in Europe, Russia, and the North America. The company is listed on the Frankfurt Stock Exchange, and in 2014 it had revenues of EUR 112bn and it employs globally more than 58,500 people. 2015.10.01 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1

ORIGINAL: U.S. mining company Newmont Mining Corp announced that it has agreed to acquire the Cripple Creek and Victor (CC&V) gold mine in the U.S. state of Colorado from South African peer AngloGold Ashanti for USD 820mn. The transaction also includes a 2.5% net smelter return royalty for gold production from potential future underground ore. The deal is expected to close in the third quarter of 2015. AngloGold Ashanti said that the sale forms part of its strategy to cut debt. Newmont, in turn, said that CC&V represents a value-accretive opportunity to improve mine life and costs in a favorable jurisdiction. The company added that it believes it can lower direct mining costs by up to 10% through improved productivity and optimisation. The Cripple Creek and Victor mine is located near Colorado Springs in Teller County and has been in operation since 1995. Newmont Mining Corp was founded in 1931 and is focused on the production of gold and copper. The company has some 28,000 employees and contractors and its major operations are located in the USA, Australia, New Zealand, Ghana, Peru, Suriname and Indonesia. Earlier this month, on 13 July 2015, CFI said it sold its entire direct interest in TgP of 1.14% for USD 25.7mn to Spanish natural gas distributor Enagas SA and to Canadian investment firm Carmen Corp. ORIGINAL: Peruvian investment firm Corporacion Financiera de Inversiones SA (CFI) announced it has agreed to acquire, via its Canada-based subsidiary La Habanera LP, a 7.25% stake in Peruvian gas pipeline operator Transportadora de Gas del Peru SA (TgP) from South Korean oil & gas company SK Innovation Co Ltd for USD 162.6mn. Following completion of this deal, the Korean firm will no longer hold any interest in TgP. Simultaneously, on 2 June 2015, Spanish natural gas distributor Enagas SA announced it has agreed to acquire a 4.34% stake in TgP for USD 97mn. Enagas will purchase 3.94% interest from SK Innovation and 0.4% from CFI. CFI acted via its Canadian subsidiary La Habanera LP. In a similar announcement, again on 2 June 2015, CFI said it has agreed to sell its entire direct interest in TgP of 1.14% for USD 25.7mn to Enagas and to Canadian investment firm Carmen Corp. As a result, a 0.74% direct stake of CFI in TgP will be purchased by Carmen, with the other 0.4% to be bought by Enagas. TgP is the largest transportation company of natural gas and gas liquids in Peru. ORIGINAL: Spanish natural gas distributor Enagas SA announced it has agreed to acquire a 4.34% stake in Peruvian gas pipeline operator Transportadora de Gas del Peru SA (TgP) for USD 97mn. Enagas will purchase 3.94% interest from South Korean oil & gas company SK Innovation Co Ltd and 0.4% from Peruvian investment firm Corporacion Financiera de Inversiones SA (CFI). Simultaneously, on 2 June 2015, CFI said it has agreed to sell its entire direct interest in TgP of 1.14% for USD 25.7mn to Enagas and to Canadian investment firm Carmen Corp. As a result, a 0.74% direct stake of CFI in TgP will be purchased by Carmen, with the other 0.4% to be bought by Enagas. In a similar announcement, again on 2 June 2015, CFI announced it has agreed to acquire, via its Canada-based subsidiary La Habanera LP, a 7.25% stake in TgP from SK Innovation for USD 162.6mn. Following completion of this deal, the Korean firm will no longer hold any interest in TgP. Enagas said that with this acquisition the company consolidates its position in Peru as a strategic operator of energy assets, and that it strengthens its long-term commitment to the country. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals. Following completion of this deal, Enagas will increase its interest in TgP from 20% to 24.34%, becoming the second largest shareholder of the Peruvian company. The Spanish firm completed the purchase of the 20% participation in TgP back in March 2014 for approximately USD 400mn. TGP is the largest transportation company of natural gas and gas liquids in Peru. The company has a network of 838 km of pipelines with a natural gas transport capacity of 1,230 million cubic feet per day and 560 km of pipelines with a capacity of 130,000 barrels/day, which transport gas from the Camisea fields, Peruvian Amazon region, to the Peru LNG natural gas liquefaction plant, located in Pampa Melchorita, and to the city of Lima. TGP reported sales revenues of USD 537.9mn and net income of USD 107mn for 2014. Enagas is the main natural gas distributor in Spain, specialized in the construction, maintenance, and operation of basic gas infrastructure. The company operates a network of 10,000 km of pipelines across Spain, three underground storage facilities and four regasification plants. In Latin America, Enagas is present in Chile, Mexico and Peru. It reported sales revenues of EUR 1.2bn (USD 1.34bn) and net income of EUR 406.5mn (USD 452mn) for 2014. SK Innovation is dedicated to the exploration and production of liquefied natural gas and oil in South Korea and internationally. The company also manufactures and distributes petroleum and petrochemical products, lubricants, base oils, polymers, lithium batteries and others. It reported sales revenues of KRW 65.9tn (USD 59.5bn) and net loss of KRW 588.8bn (USD 530mn) for 2014. Corporacion Financiera is an investment firm with USD 70mn in assets under management, specialized in investments in energy, infrastructure, agricultural and real estate projects in Peru. 2015.09.15 2938.09 2235.02 703.07 537.87 299.72 229.21 107.04 负值 55.70 69.70 来源 1 来源 2 2.35 财政年度 2014 Q1 2015

The company operates six offices worldwide and engages 130 professionals. QED Investors, based in Alexandria, Virginia, USA, is a private equity and venture capital firm focused on growth capital investments. Under the deal. Tata Sons will pay Swala a total of USD 5.7mn in cash as consideration towards the past costs incurred on the licences; Also, Tata Sons will free carry Swala through the costs of the initial wells on the licenses up to a maximum of USD 4.63mn. Tata Sons will also pay Swala up to a further USD 1mn towards the cost of a second well following a commercial discovery in the initial well on the Kilosa-Kilombero licence. Costs incurred above this sum shall be shared by the partners in proportion to their equity. Swala said that the deal allow it to remain committed to these licences and to secure funding for future exploration activities in a way that minimises the risk to its current shareholders. The Kilosa-Kilombero Licence covers an area of 17,675 km2 and is located on the East African Rift System (EARS). More than two billion barrels of oil have been found in the Lake Albert area of Uganda, which forms parts of the western branch of the EARS. The Pangani Licence has an area of 17,156 km2 and is located in the Pangani Rift. The rift also forms part of the EARS. Tata Sons Ltd is the promoter of the major operating companies of the Tata Group. The company owns the Tata name and several Tata trademarks and Tata family members own a 66% stake in it. ERS Midstream LLC is a natural gas and shale firm that designs, constructs, owns, and operates gas gathering, treating, stabilizing, and transportation services in the Eagle Ford shale trend in Texas. The company's infrastructure includes 460 miles of natural gas gathering pipelines, 10 central gathering plants, 780 million cubic feet per day of natural gas treating capacity and 119 thousand barrels per day of condensate stabilization capacity. Pioneer Natural Resources is a U.S-based independent oil and gas company operating in Texas. It has around 4,000 employees and produces 182,000 barrels of oil daily. It reported consolidated net revenues of USD 5.1bn for FY ended 31 December, 2014. Reliance Industries is an Indian conglomerate with business units in the oil and gas, chemicals, retail, textiles and telecommunications industry. ORIGINAL: British multinational tobacco company British American Tobacco (BAT) Plc announced that it will acquire Croatian cigarette manufacturer and retailer TDR d.o.o. from Croatian tobacco and tourism company Adris Grupa for an enterprise value of EUR 550mn (USD 604.3mn). The transaction also includes companies from Adris Grupa's tobacco business division, such as tobacco packaging producer Istragrafika d.d., tobacco processing and producer Hrvatski duhani d.d. and retail chains iNovine and Opresa. The transaction values TDR at an implied EV/EBITDA multiple of 12.5x. The deal is subject to anti-trust approvals and is expected to complete by October 2015. The acquisition will expand BAT's business operations in new Central European markets, including Croatia, Bosnia and Serbia. As part of the deal, BAT pledged to keep TDR's production in Kanfanar, northwestern Croatia, for at least five years after the deal is completed and to provide additional EUR 50mn in the case of early closure. BAT also intends to boost its operations in Brazil by acquiring the remaining 24.7% it does not own of local cigarette manufacturer Souza Cruz SA for BRL 10.11bn (USD 3.56bn). TDR has operations in Croatia, Bosnia and Serbia. The company has a leading position in Central Europe with a 25% market share. The company employs over 57,000 people and it posted revenues of GBP 42.5bn (USD 23.03bn), and a net profit of GBP 3.4bn (USD 5.6bn) in 2014. ORIGINAL: Colombia-focused Canadian oil & gas firm Platino Energy Corp announced it has signed an agreement pursuant to which an affiliate of a fund managed by U.S. private equity firm Denham Capital Management LP will acquire all of the outstanding common shares of Platino for CAD 0.25 (USD 0.201). Currently, Platino Energy has 74.4 million shares outstanding on a fully-diluted basis, which brings the deal value at CAD 18.6mn (approximately USD 15mn). Denham Capital Management will act via 1899072 Alberta Ltd (AcquireCo), a wholly-owned subsidiary of 1901558 Alberta Ltd (HoldCo), which in turn is the affiliate of the fund operated by Denham. Under the agreement, Platino Energy and 1899072 Alberta Ltd will merger and will form Colombia Oil and Gas Subsidiary Ltd (Amalco). Immediately after the merger, Amalco will also absorb 1901558 Alberta. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals. Platino Energy said that the sale is a result of the inability of the company to secure sufficient external funding from the public; and of the drop in oil prices, which also led to a reduction of its borrowing ability under its existing credit facility. Platino added that all this has negatively impacted its ability to execute its operational activities. Platino Energy is engaged in the exploration, acquisition, development and production of hydrocarbons in Colombia. The company was formed as a result of the purchase by Colombia-focused, Canadian oil & gas company Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp of Colombian peer C&C Energia Ltd for USD 625mn back in December 2012. Under the terms of the acquisition agreement, Pacific Rubiales acquired all of C&C Energia's common shares in exchange for 0.3528 common shares of Pacific Rubiales, USD 0.001 in cash, and one common share of the newly-established exploration company Platino Energy Corp. Platino Energy reported sales revenues of USD 1.36mn and net loss of USD 28.6mn for 2014. ORIGINAL: Singapore-based optoelectronic components developer Avago Technologies announced it will acquire U.S. counterpart Broadcom Corporation in a cash and stock deal worth USD 37bn. The transaction has been approved by the Boards of both companies. The deal is subject to regulatory approvals and it is expected to complete in the first quarter of 2016. Avago will pay Broadcom shareholders USD 17bn in cash and with 140 million own shares, equal to a 32% stake and valued at USD 20bn as of 27 May 2015, for a total purchase consideration of USD 37bn. Following the deal, shareholders of Broadcam Corporation will hold a 32% stake in the combined company, which will be named Broadcom Ltd. and will be based in Singapore. Upon completion of the deal, the combined company will have an enterprise value of USD 77bn. The deal is the largest ever transaction in the technology industry to date and Broadcom Ltd. will become a global diversified leader in wired and wireless communication semiconductors. Avago intends to fund the USD 17bn consideration with cash on hand and with USD 9bn in debt from a consortium of banks. Hock Tan, CEO of Avago, will retain his position in Broadcom Ltd., while Dr. Henry Samueli and Dr. Henry Nicholas, founders of Broadcom Corporation, will hold the roles of Chief Technology Officer and an advisor, respectively. Broadcom Corporation, founded in 1991, provides semiconductor solutions for wired and wireless communications. Its products deliver voice, video, data and multimedia connectivity in the home, office and mobile environments. The company is listed on the NASDAQ exchange. For 2014, it booked revenues of USD 8.43bn and a net profit of USD 652mn. The company employs more than 10,000. Avago Technologies Ltd designs, develops and supplies a broad range of analog semiconductor devices. Its products serve the wireless communications, wired infrastructure, and industrial markets. The company's shares are traded on NASDAQ and in 2014 it posted revenues of USD 4.26bn. 2016.04.12 36916.00 37000.00 -84.00 8428.00 1044.00 694.00 652.00 负值 12.40 15.00 来源 1 来源 2 负值 财政年度 2014 Q1 2015

ORIGINAL: Brazilian investment bank Banco BTG Pactual SA and majority shareholder Moll family announced the sale of a 15.3% stake in Brazilian hospital operator Rede D'Or Sao Luiz SA to Singapore's sovereign wealth fund GIC Private Ltd for BRL 3.2bn (USD 1.026mn). The group has an international investment and distribution platform with a team of more than 3,000 professionals across offices throughout Latin America, the United States, the United Kingdom, Singapore and Hong Kong. BTG Pactual posted a net income of BRL 1.9bn (USD 707.5bn) in 2014. BTG is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. GIC Private Ltd, incorporated in 1981, is the sovereign wealth fund of the Government of Singapore, with over USD 100bn of assets under management, focused on investments in public and private equities, fixed income assets, real estate, natural resources and infrastructure in more than 40 countries worldwide. ORIGINAL: Canadian miner Ivanhoe Mines Ltd announced it has signed an agreement to sell a 49.5% stake in Kamoa Holding Limited, holder of 95% of the Kamoa copper project located in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), to Chinese peer Zijin Mining Group Co Ltd for USD 412mn. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals, and is expected to close by 31 July 2015. Ivanhoe Mines said that it has also agreed to sell an additional 1% interest in Kamoa Holding to Crystal River Global Ltd, a private investment company incorporated in the British Virgin Islands but operated from Hong Kong. Ivanhoe Mines added that Zijin holds an option to acquire the 1% stake sold to Crystal River Global, on the condition that it manages to arrange or procure project financing for 65% of the first phase of the Kamoa copper project's development costs. The option expires in seven years from the delivery of the feasibility study, and if it is not exercised within the specified time, Ivanhoe Mines and Zijin will have the right to purchase one half of the 1%, which will result in both companies owning an equal stake of 50% in Kamoa Holding. In case Zijin Mining acquires the 1% stake, it will have to arrange project financing for the remaining development phases of the Kamoa project. Today's acquisition agreement follows Zijin Mining's recent purchase of a 9.9% interest in Ivanhoe for CAD 104.5mn (USD 83.2mn), in a deal to be implemented as a private placement of new shares. The Kamoa copper project is a newly discovered stratiform copper deposit located within the Central African Copperbelt, approximately 25 kilometres west from the DRC town of Kolwezi. Ivanhoe Mines engages in platinum, palladium, nickel, copper, gold and rhodium mining in South Africa and the Democratic Republic of Congo. The company operates three projects, two of which in the Democratic Republic of Congo and one in South Africa. It reported net loss of USD 223.2mn for 2014. Zijin Mining Group focuses on exploration, mining, processing, refining and sale of gold and non-ferrous metals. In addition, the acquisition will offer further non-auto sector diversification for Amtek Auto and will enhance its market position in Europe. Following the acquisition, REGE will provide machining and assembly of components for both auto and non-auto segments through its subsidiaries. This is the second acquisition in less than a month and the third overseas acquisition for Amtek since the beginning of 2015. Earlier in April 2015, it has agreed to acquire iron casting, forging and machining business of Japan-based Asahi Tec Corporation, which has operations in Japan, Thailand and China. In March 2015, it acquired 100% stake in German-based forging producer and speciality steel trader Scholz Edelstahl GmbH. In 2014, Amtek Auto acquired Germany-based Kuepper Group, which has aluminium casting and integrated machining operations with five manufacturing facilities across Germany and Hungary. REGE Holding, founded in 1987 and its key products include common rails, connecting rods, crankcases, cylinder heads, gear housings and valve bodies for the automotive industry. It has three plants, two in Germany and one in Romania. Its costumers portfolio include Continental, General Motors, Kia Motors, Nemak and Volkswagen. The company has more than 1,400 employees across all locations and for 2014, it recorded revenues of EUR 200mn. Amtek Auto, incorporated in 1985, is engaged in the manufacturing of various automotive machined and forged components with around 60 facilities in India, the U.K., Germany, Brazil, Italy, Mexico, Russia and the USA. It is also engaged in non-automotive components manufacturing of infrastructure, aerospace, agricultural and heavy earth moving equipment. Amtek Auto reported consolidated net revenues of INR 105.7bn (USD 1.7bn) for 15 months period ended 30 September 2013. 2015.10.21 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1 　 　 财政年度 2014

The company operates 224 branches in Mainland China, 13 branches in Hong Kong, New York, Tokyo, Singapore, Seoul, Frankfurt, Macau, Ho Chi Minh City, Sydney, San Francisco, and Taipei, as well as 2,785 banking outlets in China. ORIGINAL: Brazilian oil and gas exploration company HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA announced it has signed a definitive agreement for the sale of its 55% stake in in two Amazonian exploration blocks in the Solimoes Basin, Northern Brazil to Russian state-controlled oil major Rosneft from for USD 55mn. The buyer acted through its Brazilian subsidiary Rosneft Brasil E&P Ltda. The deal aligns with PetroRio's plan to focus on oilfields already operating. In the press statement, the company said it is now driven to "oil fields already in production, re-exploration, growth of operational efficiency, reduction in production costs and corporate expenses". The agreement is subject to regulatory approvals and the fulfilment of certain conditions. Following the deal, Rosneft will consolidate its equity interest to 100%. Rosneft, established in 1993, is a vertically-integrated oil and gas company, controlled by the Government of Russia, engaged in the exploration, production and sale of crude oil and gas, and refining, transportation, and sale of petrochemical products. The company has total proved hydrocarbon reserves of 22.8 billion barrels of oil equivalent and has operations in Russia, Kazakhstan and Algeria. Rosneft is listed on the Moscow and London Stock Exchanges. PortoRio S.A., (former HRT), founded in 2009 in Rio de Janeiro, is an oil and gas company with a portfolio of 29 exploration onshore and offshore blocks with estimated reserves of 7.9 billion barrels of oil equivalent, and a 60% stake in the active Polvo oil field in Campos Basin, with average production of 13,000 barrels of oil per day. The group includes six companies: HRT Oil & Gas (operator of 19 blocks in the Solimoes Basin, Amazonas state, and three blocks in the states of Bahia, Espirito Santo, and Paraiba), HRT Africa (owner of 10 blocks in offshore Namibia), HRT America and HRT Canada (geological and geophysical researches), HRT Netherlands (commercial support services) and IPEX (geological research and analysis). PetroRio posted BRL 486.8mn (USD 149.6) in revenues and a net loss of BRL 1bn (USD 308.2mn) in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. ____________________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 14 de outubro de 2015 a Rosneft anunciou que o negócio foi concluído. ORIGINAL: U.K.-based energy and environment assets holding company Abengoa Yield PLC announced that it has agreed to acquire a package of four solar assets in Spain and South Africa from Spanish engineering and clean technology firm Abengoa SA for USD 669mn. The power plant is capable of providing power to some 80,000 homes. Abengoa Yield is a dividend growth-oriented company established in December 2013 by Abengoa in order to own a portfolio of renewable energy, conventional power and electric transmission assets located primarily in North and South America, and previously owned by Abengoa and its subsidiaries. Abengoa Yield is listed on the NASDAQ Stock Market and had a market capitalisation of USD 2.89bn on 11 May 2015. JD.com will become the largest shareholder of Tuniu with a 27.5% stake upon deal completion. Other investors include Unicorn Riches Ltd, an affiliate of Hony Capital, DCM Ventures China Turbo Fund LP and DCM Ventures China Turbo Affiliates Fund LP, both affiliates of DCM V LP, Ctrip Investment Holding Ltd, subsidiary of Ctrip.com International Ltd, Esta Investments Pte Ltd, an affiliate of Temasek Holdings, Sequoia Capital 2010 CV Holdco Ltd, an affiliate of Sequoia Capital. Unicorn, DCM Ventures China Turbo Fund, DCM Ventures China Turbo Affiliates Fund, Ctrip Investment, Esta Investments and Sequoia Capital will invest USD 80mn, USD 20mn, USD 20mn, USD 20mn and USD 10mn, respectively, in the private placement. The transaction marks the second investment of JD.com in Tuniu as it also took part in the latter's private placement, which raised USD 148mn in December 2014, giving JD.com a 6.5% stake. Tuniu and JD.com also announced they will form a partnership in which Tuniu will have control of JD.com's website and mobile app, and make JD.com its preferred hotel and air tickets booking services partner. Tuniu Corp offers packaged tours, organized tours and various travel-related services through its online and mobile platforms, call centers and service centers. The company's packaged tours cover 140 countries worldwide. Tuniu Corp is listed on the NASDAQ and recorded revenues of USD 572.9mn in 2014. JD.com operates as one of the largest online direct sales companies in China and offers mobile applications, products and services through its website JD.com. The company recorded revenues of USD 11.5bn in 2013. Note 1: The new shares were calculated by dividing the USD 500mn investment to the purchase price of USD 5.33 per ordinary share of Tuniu. The deal stake was calculated using the outstanding shares of Tuniu for FY 31 December 2014 and the estimated 93,808,630 new shares.
